== Japanese content ==
{{座標一覧}}
'''Kamo Shrine''' (かもじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} recorded as "Kamo Jinja" in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki|Q1342448|qid=Q1342448|1=Engishiki}} {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyocho|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=Register of Shrines|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} under {{ill|lt=Sanuki Province|Q929682|qid=Q929682|1=Sanuki Province}}{{ill|lt=Aya District|Q11658001|qid=Q11658001|1=Aya district}}. In {{ill|lt=Sakaide|Q855059|qid=Q855059|1=Sakaide, Kagawa}}, {{ill|lt=Kagawa Prefecture|Q161454|qid=Q161454|1=Kagawa Prefecture}}, there are the following two candidate shrines ({{ill|lt=ronsha|Q135022904|qid=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}}).

# {{ill|lt=Kamo Shrine (Sakaide)#Higashi Kamo Shrine|Q11675600|qid=Q11675600|lt=Higashi Kamo Shrine|1=Kamo Shrine (Sakaide)}} (992 Kamo-chō, {{ill|lt=Sakaide|Q855059|qid=Q855059|1=Sakaide, Kagawa}}, {{ill|lt=Kagawa Prefecture|Q161454|qid=Q161454|1=Kagawa Prefecture}}) - former {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.
# {{ill|lt=Kamo Shrine (Sakaide)#Nishi Kamo Shrine|Q11675600|qid=Q11675600|lt=Nishi Kamo Shrine|1=Kamo Shrine (Sakaide)}} (540 Kamo-chō, Sakaide, Kagawa Prefecture) - former village shrine.

=== Overview ===
Kamo Shrine as a Shikinaisha is listed in the ''Engishiki'' register and is also recorded in the ''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|qid=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}'' as having been granted court rank. The area preserves the old toponym of Kamo-be-go in Aya District in ancient times<ref>''Place Names of Kagawa Prefecture'', section on Kamo Village.</ref>. Today there are two shrines, east and west, and there is no established consensus as to which one should be identified as the Engishiki shrine<ref name="鴨神社">''Place Names of Kagawa Prefecture'', section on Kamo Shrine.</ref>.

=== Ranks granted to the deity ===
* {{ill|lt=Jogan (Japan)|Q1075635|qid=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan|1=Jōgan}} 7 ({{ill|lt=865|Q30350|qid=Q30350|1=865}}), 10th month 9th day: promoted from junior fifth rank lower to junior fifth rank upper (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|qid=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}'') - written as "Kamo-no-kami"
* Jōgan 17 ({{ill|lt=875|Q23816|qid=Q23816|1=875}}), 5th month 27th day: senior fifth rank lower (''Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku'') - written as "Kamo Tenjin"

